          <h2>Answers</h2> 
          
          <p id="start"><strong>As a student, I need a house in the autumn, how do I go about getting one in Guildford?</strong></p>
          <p>Big question! The best time to start is when you have a group of 5 or 6, then start looking towards the end of your 
          first term - November is not too early .Then you need to look through our housing list and see if there is one you like. 
          Click on <strong><%= link_to "Properties", properties_path %></strong> and scroll down the list. Clicking on an address 
          takes you to more information about the house, and more pictures.</p>
          
          <p id="secure"><strong>If I like a house on your website what do I do?</strong></p>
          <p>It is always a good idea to arrange a viewing. Photos can be deceptive, and you ought to see the room and how it feels 
          before you commit. You may like to send your parents a link to the website so they can see the house as they may like to 
          visit with you. Once agreed, you place a Holding Deposit of &pound;450, and we carry out credit checks on your guarantor. 
          It is always a good idea to arrange a viewing. Photos can be deceptive, and you ought to see the room and how it feels 
